{
  "stem": "13469.5",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And so that night, the lists were read out, and we were all on the lists-- and-- and father and me in our barrack, and mother, Eve, and Rudy in the other barrack, they were all on the list.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And we got together later on.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And next morning, we all appeared, and we all went on the train.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We knew we were going to Bergen-Belsen, because that apparently had been mentioned, discussed, earlier.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In-- in January, in Westerbork, we were all told that we were going to go to a camp called-- called Bergen-Belsen, and it was all these exchange people.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we assumed that it wouldn't be too bad.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, we had no idea.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We'd never heard of the name, Bergen-Belsen, before.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Perhaps I-- I should mention that I have read that some people from Westerbork actually went to another camp in France, called Vittel, and these were people who had British, mainly American, passports.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We didn't really notice that-- whether my parents noticed it, I-- I don't know.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But this may have been the difference between them actually have passports and us only having a birth certificate.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because we can't understand why they were sent to Vittel, and-- and we were not.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we were sent to Bergen-Belsen, which was much worse, because the people in Vittel apparently all got out.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And Vittel apparently was a very good camp-- it was like a hotel.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So we've heard after the war.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But I don't understand-- all sorts of things went on all the time where we never really figured out why, or what was happening.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was all via some underground rumors, kind of things, about what people thought was happening.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Anyway, we went to Bergen-Belsen.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not a lot.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I presume that we were all together in the compartment.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
